cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the construction of space-time block codes and uses the Diversity Multiplexing Tradeoff as a tool to evaluate the performance, which are both topics related to information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a Multi-Access Amplify-and-Forward Relay channel with two users and a single half-duplex relay, which is a networking and internet architecture problem.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheme for the relay channel, which can be seen as a control problem in systems and control.
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with the design of a communication scheme for a relay channel, which falls under the communication and networking category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper's use of space-time block codes can be applied to multimedia transmission, making this category a possibility.
